.TH "smk_ptrace_rule_check" 9 "smk_ptrace_rule_check" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
smk_ptrace_rule_check \- helper for ptrace access
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" smk_ptrace_rule_check
.BI "(struct task_struct *tracer "  ","
.BI "struct smack_known *tracee_known "  ","
.BI "unsigned int mode "  ","
.BI "const char *func "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "tracer" 12
tracer process
.IP "tracee_known" 12
label entry of the process that's about to be traced
.IP "mode" 12
ptrace attachment mode (PTRACE_MODE_*)
.IP "func" 12
name of the function that called us, used for audit
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns 0 on access granted, -error on error
